description:
We continue to explore the work of John Huss and Jerome of Bohemia. In 1415, the Council of Constance (Konstanz) convened to settle the Papal Schism and deal with 'heresies' that were arising. John Huss was called to trial, and Jerome came seeking to help him. Unfortunately, Jerome ended up in prison himself, where he went on to initially renounce the teachings of John Huss.

To find out more about Huss & Jerome read our extended article on their lives.
http://www.lineagejourney.com/reformation/reformers/huss-jerome-catalysts-bohemian-reformation/
